{"info": {"author": "Jason Hamilton-Smith", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Topic :: Documentation", "Topic :: Text Processing :: Markup"], "description": "Vidify - convert img tags to html5 video tags\n================================================================================\n\nVidify is a plugin for Python's Markdown that allows you to embed html5 video\ninto your document. It's inteneded for Python 3.6 + but is _probably_\nback-compatible with 2.7.\n\nVidifiy works by detecting `<img>` tags pointing at a file with an extension of\n.webm, .mp4, or .ogg and replacing them with `<video>` tags.\n\nInstalling\n---\nSimply install from PyPi:\n```\npip install markdown-vidify\n```\n\nUsage\n================================================================================\nSimply import the package and then pass it to the extensions parameter of\nmarkdown!\n```python\nimport markdown\nimport markdown_vidify\n\n# ...\n\nouptut = markdown.markdown(input, extensions=[\n    markdown_vidify.VidifyExtension(\n        autoplay=False,\n        controls=True,\n        loop=False,\n        mute=False,\n    )\n])\n```\n\nOptions\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nAll default to false:\n\n* autoplay - Autoplay the video once page is loaded\n* controls - Display player controls below the video\n* loop - Loop the video\n* mute - Video is muted by default\n\nExtra Hints!\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nConsider using the Attribute List plugin that comes with markdown to set the\nhtml5 poster attribute. This will be an image that displays in-place of your\nvideo while it is downloading or until the user hits the play button!\n\n```\n![alt](/path/to/video.webm){: poster=\"/path/to/image.png\"}\n```\n\nWeird Caveat\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nSince html5 video doesn't have an alt-text, the body of the [] is entirely\nignored. Other plugins may still use it however. I am aware of how -janky- this\nis. I considered using it for the poster tag but that still feels janky and it\nwould also interfere with other markdown plugins. If you feel you haev a good\nusgesstion feel free to post it as an issue.\n\nBoring Stuff\n================================================================================\nvidify was written by Jason Hamilton-Smith `<hs.jason@gmail.com>`, my website is\n[zchfvy.com](https://zchfvy.com).\n\nThis project is licensed under the GPL v3.0 license. See the `LICENSE` file for\ndetails.\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/zchfvy/vidify", "keywords": "makrdown video html5 html5video", "license": "GPLv3", "maintainer": "Jason Hamilton-Smith", "maintainer_email": "hs.jason@gmail.com", "name": "markdown-vidify", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/markdown-vidify/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/markdown-vidify/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/zchfvy/vidify"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/markdown-vidify/0.1.1/", "requires_dist": ["markdown (<4,>=3.2.1)"], "requires_python": ">=2.7.15, !=3.0.*, !=3.1.*, !=3.2.*, !=3.3.*, !=3.4.*, !=3.5.*", "summary": "Video tag generator markdown extension", "version": "0.1.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Vidify - convert img tags to html5 video tags</h1>\n<p>Vidify is a plugin for Python's Markdown that allows you to embed html5 video\ninto your document. It's inteneded for Python 3.6 + but is <em>probably</em>\nback-compatible with 2.7.</p>\n<p>Vidifiy works by detecting <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tags pointing at a file with an extension of\n.webm, .mp4, or .ogg and replacing them with <code>&lt;video&gt;</code> tags.</p>\n<h2>Installing</h2>\n<p>Simply install from PyPi:</p>\n<pre><code>pip install markdown-vidify\n</code></pre>\n<h1>Usage</h1>\n<p>Simply import the package and then pass it to the extensions parameter of\nmarkdown!</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">markdown</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">markdown_vidify</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># ...</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">ouptut</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">markdown</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">markdown</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">input</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">extensions</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"p\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">markdown_vidify</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">VidifyExtension</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">autoplay</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"kc\">False</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">controls</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"kc\">True</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">loop</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"kc\">False</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"n\">mute</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"kc\">False</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"p\">])</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>Options</h2>\n<p>All default to false:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>autoplay - Autoplay the video once page is loaded</li>\n<li>controls - Display player controls below the video</li>\n<li>loop - Loop the video</li>\n<li>mute - Video is muted by default</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Extra Hints!</h2>\n<p>Consider using the Attribute List plugin that comes with markdown to set the\nhtml5 poster attribute. This will be an image that displays in-place of your\nvideo while it is downloading or until the user hits the play button!</p>\n<pre><code>![alt](/path/to/video.webm){: poster=\"/path/to/image.png\"}\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Weird Caveat</h2>\n<p>Since html5 video doesn't have an alt-text, the body of the [] is entirely\nignored. Other plugins may still use it however. I am aware of how -janky- this\nis. I considered using it for the poster tag but that still feels janky and it\nwould also interfere with other markdown plugins. If you feel you haev a good\nusgesstion feel free to post it as an issue.</p>\n<h1>Boring Stuff</h1>\n<p>vidify was written by Jason Hamilton-Smith <code>&lt;hs.jason@gmail.com&gt;</code>, my website is\n<a href=\"https://zchfvy.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">zchfvy.com</a>.</p>\n<p>This project is licensed under the GPL v3.0 license. See the <code>LICENSE</code> file for\ndetails.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6727038, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "710325944d4238d2283d1c59889cd9cb", "sha256": "eae252f85c06a2a2dcda5db9c6d038a023e06094edc827e37dafc0ae7ce5d999"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "markdown_vidify-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "710325944d4238d2283d1c59889cd9cb", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=2.7.15, !=3.0.*, !=3.1.*, !=3.2.*, !=3.3.*, !=3.4.*, !=3.5.*", "size": 16738, "upload_time": "2020-03-01T03:38:14", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-01T03:38:14.324736Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/01/fe/8849e646ed8fe11b3c6056e0ca043dcf0b2a745fbaf3467a5ea825edba07/markdown_vidify-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "6249ed6021101d37f510e02664598f79", "sha256": "b5173530a19433202e68677ef6dfc52f5a69b52036d9be4c60f1241ff81acf8e"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "markdown-vidify-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "6249ed6021101d37f510e02664598f79",